Title: Basic Representations of A_{2l}^(2) and D_{l+1}^(2) and the Polynomial

Solutions to the Reduced BKP HierarchiesAuthors: Tatsuhiro Nakajima and Hirofumi Yamada (Tokyo Metropolitan U.)

Comments: January 1994, 11 pages

Journal-ref: J.Phys. A27 (1994) L171-L176

Basic representations of A_{2l}^(2) and D_{l+1}^(2) are studied. The weightvectors are represented in terms of Schur's $Q$-functions. The method to getthe polynomial solutions to the reduced BKP hierarchies is shown to beequivalent to a certain rule in Maya game.